Package sg.dex.starfish

Interface Job<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of result returned by the Job
    All Superinterfaces:
    Future<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MemoryJob, RemoteJob
    public interface Job<T>
extends Future<T>
    Interface representing an asynchronous job execution. Job extends the Future interface, but adds additional functionality relevant to invokable services in the data ecosystem. Jobs are typically executed via the Invoke API
    Version:
    0.5
    Author:
    Mike

      • getJobID

        String getJobID()
        Gets the Job ID associated with this Job. Job IDs are allocated by the agent implementation responsible for completing the job, and may be used to refer to the Job via other mechanisms.
        Returns:
        jobID

        T pollResult()
        Gets the result of the Job if available, or null if not yet available. If null is a possible result of the operation, it is recommended to check isDone() first.
        Returns:
        The Asset resulting from the job, or null if not yet available
